ratings.comment: Doesn't like when students question things
Class was an absolute joke. She would read off her slides word for word and would be unable to answer any questions students had. Not helpful. A shame that one of our nursing fundamentals was so bad.

I was so excited for this class but was extremely disappointed with Diane. Lectures consisted of multiple 80 some slide powerpoints which were copied from the book and she simply reads word for word off of them. There were multiple times where she would skip over a term stating she didnt have time to look it up. Exams were riddled with mistakes.
She is very personable and friendly. Youll learn a lot in a short amount of time. She makes me really excited to be a nurse.
She really know what shes talking about. The class is hard but if you work for it you can get a good grade. Overall very good professor.

This was supposed to be a class FUNDAMENTAL to our nursing content, yet I am walking away with nothing. Diane uses pre-made slides from the textbook company which are often irrelevant. Unprepared for lectures and strictly reads from the powerpoint. Two exams, each worth 30% and they are so poorly written that it's impossible to do well.
